  "text": "Pigs have the most diverse collection of cathelicidins of any mammalian species, among which are the prolinephenylalanine-rich prophenin-1 (PF-1), prophenin-2 (PF-2), proline-arginine-rich PR-39, and cysteine-rich protegrins 1 to 5 (PG-1 to PG-5), which have been purified from neutrophils [CITATION_1] .",
